channel.title: Lost Client :\
channel.description: i just deleted my .java client files by mistake from my client folder, and my backup was deleted somehow.. my recycle bin is DELETED. i only have the .class files now on my client.. will java decompilers work well and recover my client? :(

item.title: Lost Client :\
item.dc:creator: @eyeownyew Eyeownyew
item.description:
@eyeownyew wrote:

[quote=“Lin, post:11, topic:376990”][quote author=flj0yter0p link=topic=472909.msg3459104#msg3459104 date=1294316245]

[quote author=RuneSpace link=topic=472909.msg3459085#msg3459085 date=1294313341]

Use those file recovering tools, i’ve recovered lots of stuff thanks to those.

Google something like “Restore deleted files”.

You mean Spyware? Download Spyware, Trojan and a Keylogger. Will restore all code, and does a background check from what yu delete’

Can find easy on google
[/quote]So you’re saying this for example software: http://www.recovermyfiles.com/ worth $69 is spyware?
[/quote]That’s probably something like DropBox where all of your files are uploaded online to later download. If not, it’s impossible to recover anything emptied from the Recycle Bin, hence the warning message that comes up when you try to do so…[/quote]

There’s always the trick of using Binary.
Yet, it’s really not worth it to decode something that complicated in Binary, when you can just find another…
